se64\\nfrom flask_socketio import SocketIO, emit\\n\\n# Initialize Flask app and SocketIO\\napp = Flask(__name__)\\nsocketio = SocketIO(app)\\n\\n# Route for the main page\\n@app.route(\'/\')\\ndef index():\\n    return render_template(\'index.html\')\\n\\n# Function to create loops\\n@socketio.on(\'create_loop\')\\ndef handle_create_loop(data):\\n    # Implement loop creation logic here\\n    loop = data[\'loop\']\\n    # For demonstration, just echo the loop back\\n    emit(\'loop_created\', {\'loop\': loop})\\n\\n# Function to analyze chord progressions\\n@socketio.on(\'analyze_progression\')\\ndef handle_analyze_progression(data):\\n    # Implement chord progression analysis logic here\\n    progression = data[\'progression\']\\n    # For demonstration, just echo the progression back\\n    emit(\'progression_analyzed\', {\'progression\': progression})\\n\\n# Function to visualize soundwaves\\n@socketio.on(\'visualize_soundwave\')\\ndef handle_visualize_soundwave(data):\\n    # Implement soundwave visualization logic here\\n    audio_file = data[\'audio_file\']\\n    # Load audio file\\n    y, sr = librosa.load(audio_file)\\n    # Create a plot\\n    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))\\n    librosa.display.waveshow(y, sr=sr)\\n    # Save plot to a buffer\\n    buf = io.BytesIO()\\n    plt.savefig(buf, format=\'png\')\\n    buf.seek(0)\\n    # Encode image to base64\\n    image_base64 = base64.b64encode(buf.getvalue()).decode(\'utf8\')\\n    emit(\'soundwave_visualized\', {\'image\': image_base64})\\n\\nif __name__ == \'__main__\':\\n    socketio.run(app, debug=True)\\n"\n}\n```\n\nThis `solution.py` sets up a basic Flask application with SocketIO for real-time collaboration. It includes placeholders for the loop creation, chord progression analysis, and soundwave visualization functionalities. The actual implementation details for these functionalities need to be filled in based on the specific requirements and technologies chosen for the project.\n\nPlease note that th